This paper discusses cooperative transmission protocols in wireless networks, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The use of multiuser detection (MUD) and network coding suggests that the paper may also fall under the systems and control (SY) category. Additionally, the paper may involve multimedia (MM) due to the use of wireless channels. Finally, the paper may also involve cryptography and security (CR) as it discusses bit error rate.
